description:
It's dinner time! On today's menu: raviolis, strawberry tarts, chocolate eclairs&hellip; Yum yum! Each player has 3 plates and must finish them as fast as possible, by using the &ldquo;Fork&rdquo; cards of the right color. And thanks to the magic fork, some lucky players will finish even more quickly. But beware! One can play nasty tricks to another by switching plates or by adding extra plates to an opponent&hellip;

A game by Pierre-Nicolas Lapointe illustrated by Arnaud Qu&eacute;r&eacute; 2 to 4 players from 6 & up. Strong points: A cute and simple game you can sink your teeth into! A variant for younger players (without the special cards) is available.

In the box: a deck of 46 cards (14 &ldquo;Plate&rdquo;, 27 &ldquo;Fork&rdquo;, 2 &ldquo;Extra Plate&rdquo;, 3 &ldquo;Plate Switch&rdquo;, 2 rule summaries)

Vermix roared as the zeppelin&rsquo;s cannons blasted into him, the great dragon screaming in terrible pain as the cannon ball smashed into his armored hide. Any other dragon might have been blow from the skies with such a volley of lead shot, but Vermix was no weakling, but rather one of the true kings of the skies. The wizards of Tor thought they could take the dragon lord&rsquo;s territory without much of a fight from the might red dragon, but these wizards were fools, for Vermix never surrendered and had yet to lose a battle for control of the clouds that he called home.

This is Cloud Wars', yet another Mini-Game from Bad Baby Production. In Cloud Wars, you and other players take on the role of mighty air ships, eagle riders and lords of cloud castles as you battle for control of the skies above a fantasy world. The first expansion for the Dragon Wars game, now players can lead forces of wizard forged zeppelins and marshal squadrons of might eagle riders. Fully compatible with Dragon War, have fun and battle for the skies.

Using a fast turn based system; the combat is swift, the excitement nail biting and the strategy intense. Do you dare enter the world of dragons, wizards and cannons&hellip;

From the press release:

Aaarr! Hoist your sails and set your course for high seas adventure in Piratack. This thrilling new board game beckons you into a world where all can join in swashbuckling fun. Players must throw caution to the winds as their ships voyage through tranquil and stormy seas or pass through whirlpools. Ships must trade cargo to increase their strength in cannons because when time runs out&hellip;
                You can&rsquo;t escape&hellip;
                                PIRATACK!
In the end, the fiercest will battle for the ultimate sovereign rule as Piratitan!

The Holiday Game is a Print and Play board game and is completely free for you to enjoy.

I should point out that I am from the UK where the word &lsquo;Holiday&rsquo; refers to a vacation &ndash; this is not a game about Christmas or Thanks giving, it is a game about swimming pools, bungee jumps, cabaret bars, nightclubs, water sports and lots more&hellip;

Home Page: http://theholidaygame.mysite.orange.co.uk

&hellip;You awaken in a small shadowy chamber lit only by a fiery brazier&hellip;a deep voice from a shimmering red figure intones &ldquo;You will plague me no longer!  You have interfered in my plans for far too long. You claim to be a hero?  Well then&hellip; let&rsquo;s put you to the test!  I have entombed you inside my maze&hellip;can you escape and prove yourself worthy of the title hero? If you can escape my maze before sunrise I shall leave your lands forever&hellip;

Maze of the Red Mage is a solitaire dungeon adventure game.  Your goal is to defeat the Red Mage by escaping before the sunrises!  If the Sun rises or you die in the maze, the Red Mage will rule your lands forever!

The dungeon is set up randomly face down using tiles.  A blend of the classic PC games Minesweeper and Rogue Maze of the Red Mage includes: variable creatures, treasures, dungeon design and characters making every game different! It includes rules to level up your character as well, all in a quick re-playable lunchtime escape!

from the publishers:

THE GAME THAT WILL REEL YOU IN, HOOK, LINE AND SINKER!
Gone Fishin&rsquo; &ndash; when grouped together, two of the most beautiful words in the English language! Fishin&rsquo;-opoly allows players to buy, sell and trade their favorite fish and gear with family and friends. Players choose their tokens and advance to Cast. It&rsquo;s all fun and games until someone lands on SNAG, gets all hung up, and is out of the game for three turns! While playing, flip over the deeds and learn some fun fishin&rsquo; facts. And you know what they say, &ldquo;A bad day of fishin&rsquo; is still better than a good day at work!&rdquo;

from the publishers:

OPEN A BOOK! THE WORLD AWAITS YOU!

Book-opoly allows players a glimpse inside the many worlds of classic literature. It&rsquo;s a traditional property trading game where players buy, sell and trade their way to fun with family and friends. Interesting facts about the books and the authors are printed on the back of each property deed. Roll the dice and advance to Read. Collect Bookstores and trade them in for Libraries. Who knows! You may soon be elected President of the Book Club&hellip;or you may be tossed out of the game for three turns and sent to WATCH TV!

from the publishers:

A CREEPING, CRAWLING, PROPERTY TRADING GAME!

Bug-opoly is a look inside the wonderful bug kingdom. Buy, sell and trade your favorite insects (and a few of their friends because not every bug included in the game is technically an insect.) As you play, flip over the deeds and read some amazing and fun facts. Gather family and friends and get buggy with it! Who knows? You may soon be elected president of the Entomological Society&hellip;or you may be sent to Bug Off, and out of the game for three turns! Whatever happens, the game will be crawling with good fun!

Combat Commander: Battle Pack #1 &ndash; Paratroopers is the first of what will be many themed collections of scenarios for use with the Combat Commander: Europe series of games. The theme of this first Battle Pack is focused on the exploits of American, German and even Russian Airborne forces. CC&ndash;Paratroopers features eleven new scenarios printed on cardstock, as well as four new maps. Future Battle Packs will be similarly structured and may also include new counters or new cards &ndash; with themes such as &ldquo;Stalingrad&rdquo;, &ldquo;Partisans&rdquo; and &ldquo;Desert Rats&rdquo; to name just a few.

COMPONENTS:
2 17" x 22" 2-sided color mapsheets
6 2-sided Scenario Cards

The scenarios included in CC&ndash;Paratroopers are:

    &ldquo;Fields of Fire&rdquo; and &ldquo;Fields of Blood&rdquo; set at Lanzerath, Germany, 16 December 1944 &ndash; both the morning and the afternoon attacks (using a new map #25);
    &ldquo;Turnbull Turns &lsquo;em&rdquo; at Neuville-au-Plain, France, 6 June 1944 (using a new map #26);
    &ldquo;Carentan Causeway&rdquo; at Carentan, France, 10 June 1944 (using a new map #27);
    &ldquo;No Ingouf Around&rdquo; at Carentan, France, 11 June 1944 (using a new map #28);
    &ldquo;Operation Repulse&rdquo; at Bastogne, Belgium, 27 December 1944;
    &ldquo;Red Skies at Night&rdquo; at Veliki Bukrin Bridgehead, Russia, 25 September 1943;
    &ldquo;Blizzard Baptism&rdquo; at Flamierge, Belgium, 4 January 1945;
    &ldquo;Look Mom, No Tanks!&rdquo; near Trois Ponts, Belgium, 24 December 1944;
    &ldquo;We Go!&rdquo; at St. Mere Eglise, France, 6 June 1944;
    &ldquo;Encircled at Hill 30&rdquo; at Caponnet, France, 8 June 1944.


NOTE: CC&ndash;Paratroopers is not a complete game and requires ownership of Combat Commander: Europe to play.

Scenario designs in this first Pack are courtesy of Will Green, John Holme, Gregory L. Wong, Bryan Collars, Ric Van Dyke, Tray Green and Dan Holte.

from the Publisher's website:

Relive many of the funniest and most memorable &ldquo;I Love Lucy&rdquo; episodes in the &ldquo;California, Here We Come&rdquo; edition of the world&rsquo;s most famous board game, MONOPOLY. Travel west with Lucy and the gang as they head to California, finding trouble and fun wherever they go. Buy, sell and trade hilarious episodes like &ldquo;L.A At Last!,&rdquo; &ldquo;Harpo Marx,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Lucy Visits Grauman&rsquo;s&rdquo; in a quest to own all of Lucy&rsquo;s California adventures. Comes complete with 6 collectible pewter tokens of Ricky&rsquo;s Convertible, Derby Hat, Harp, Cement Block, Lucy&rsquo;s Glasses and Lucy&rsquo;s Shoes.

Gather friends and family as you reminisce about Lucy&rsquo;s hilarious shenanigans in Hollywood and get ready for some good old-fashioned fun!

A promotional game developed by MeesPierson in cooperation with Identity Games.

from the rule booklet:

Trader is a dynamic board game that embraces every element of the commodity trade. The players become traders and discover whether they are experts at doing business efficiently. Trader is about making money through well-timed buying and selling of loads of commodities. Discover the strategic world of the commodity trade!

Culloden on Drummossie Moor, April 16, 1746. William Augustus, Duke of Cumberland, leads a new Government army loyal to the House of Hannover north to face Prince Charles Edward Stuart's fierce Highlanders. Bonnie Prince Charlie's Scots have been victorious in every encounter with the forces of the 'German Usurper' George II since the Jacobite flag of rebellion was raised at Glen Coe on August 19, 1745. Now as the fog lifts off the sodden moorland at 11 AM, 4500 claymore-armed clansmen, most having not eaten nor slept in a day and a half, stand to as the red-coated ranks of 9000 troops of the government army march into battle formations. As the cannon of both sides unleash grapeshot, the Duke orders his troops forward, confident in their fire discipline. The Scots, outnumbered 2 to 1 in bodies but possessing the spirit of a lion in every Celtic breast, launch themselves into an attack borne by their battle ferocity that has been victorious in every contest of arms for the past year. The throne of Britain has just been laid on the scales of combat.

Culloden contains:
one 11" by 17" map;
140 die-cut backprinted 1/2" counters;
8 pages of rules and scenarios;
Just Plain Wargames Folio Format
Cover Artwork by Adrian George

This is a kid's game for Ages 4 and up.

What a mishap, the small polar bear brought the photos completely in disorder when looking at them with his best friends . With a good memory and some luck he succeeds to build the pictures up again. Of course the player with most photos will win.

Objective: score most winning points after all slides are used
- acting by turn -
active player uncovers one (of 36 in the beginning) slide:
if it shows a lemming, keep it and draw again;
if it is part of a bigger animal: uncover as many cards as points on your slide;
if you succeed forming a complete animal, keep it; if not:
flip these tiles over and place them back on the table.
Game ends after all slides are used.

Taken from the Press Pass Inc. press release:

Press Pass, Inc. [recently] announced a licensing agreement with the Twentieth Century Fox Film Corporation for the 24&trade; TCG (Trading Card Game). Based on the action-packed drama airing every Monday night at 9:00 p.m. (8:00 p.m. Central) on Fox, the 24&trade; TCG is scheduled to launch in August 2007 and builds on the success established by Press Pass with its critically acclaimed Fullmetal Alchemist TCG.

Currently in its sixth season, 24&trade; follows the life of CTU agent Jack Bauer (played by Kiefer Sutherland) and his allies, minute by minute, through a single 24-hour day full of heart-stopping action and intense drama as they work to quell a threat to the American people. The Emmy award-winning series boasts nearly 16 million viewers each week and has inspired a wide range of licensed properties, including PlayStation2 video games, novels, comic books, and an upcoming line of action figures.

&ldquo;This is a license we&rsquo;re thrilled to get,&rdquo; said Edward Bolme, TCG Product Manager for Press Pass. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re designing this game to capture the essence of action and tension that the show portrays. We think the fans will find it a very exciting and attractive game.&rdquo;

&ldquo;Fans of 24&trade; will love this game,&rdquo; added Virginia King, Executive Director of Fox Licensing and Merchandising. &ldquo;Serious collectors who don&rsquo;t play games will want to collect these cards.&rdquo;

Created by the award-winning Press Pass, Inc. design team responsible for the Fullmetal Alchemist TCG (voted #1 New TCG of 2005 by readers of Scrye and InQuest and Best Anime TCG of 2006 by Anime Insider), the 24&trade; TCG will let you play either with or against CTU in a fast-paced struggle for victory. The game will feature 24-card decks and can be played in 15 to 20 minutes. Press Pass will also conduct a comprehensive marketing and promotion campaign as well as an aggressive tournament system.
